7.1 Performance Requirements
NFR-PERF-001

API response time SHALL remain below:

500ms for standard requests
2s for analytical queries
NFR-PERF-002

Dashboard rendering SHALL complete within 3 seconds.

NFR-PERF-003

The system SHALL support:

5,000 concurrent users
100,000 repositories
10 million stored events
7.2 Reliability Requirements
NFR-REL-001

System uptime SHALL be at least 99.5%.

NFR-REL-002

Critical failures SHALL generate alerts within 1 minute.

NFR-REL-003

Background jobs SHALL support retry behavior.

Retry Policy:

Maximum retries: 5
Exponential backoff required
7.3 Security Requirements
NFR-SEC-001

All traffic SHALL use HTTPS.

NFR-SEC-002

Sensitive data SHALL be encrypted at rest using AES-256.

NFR-SEC-003

Secrets SHALL NOT be stored in source code repositories.

NFR-SEC-004

Audit logs SHALL be immutable.

7.4 Scalability Requirements
NFR-SCALE-001

The architecture SHALL support horizontal scaling.

NFR-SCALE-002

Background processing SHALL be independently scalable.

7.5 Maintainability Requirements
NFR-MAINT-001

The system SHALL use modular boundaries.

NFR-MAINT-002

Modules SHALL expose internal APIs only through defined interfaces.

NFR-MAINT-003

All production services SHALL include structured logging.

7.6 Observability Requirements
NFR-OBS-001

The system SHALL expose:

Error metrics
Request metrics
Queue metrics
AI processing metrics
NFR-OBS-002

Logs SHALL support correlation IDs.